<section class="section shell article-layout"><nav class="article-nav" aria-label="Healthy play topics"><a href="#signs">Signs to notice</a><a href="#support">Outside support</a><a href="#facts">Parlor facts</a></nav><article class="prose"><h2 id="signs">Signs that it is time to stop</h2><ul><li>Trying to win back a fictional loss</li><li>Playing longer than intended</li><li>Feeling irritable, anxious, secretive, or unable to stop</li><li>Skipping sleep, school, work, relationships, or responsibilities</li><li>Thinking fictional results predict future outcomes</li></ul><p>Do not chase losses. No one is “due” for a win, and past random rounds do not make a future win more likely.</p><h2 id="support">Outside support</h2><p>If casino-style play is causing distress, step away and talk with someone you trust. The Adult Owner can configure current, region-appropriate support resources here. In an immediate crisis, contact local emergency services.</p><h2 id="facts">What the Parlor never offers</h2><ul><li>No real-money wagers, deposits, prizes, withdrawals, or cash out</li><li>No purchases of Cozy Coins, Parlor Stars, spins, bets, or randomized rewards</li><li>No user-to-user balance transfers</li><li>No subscriber odds or payout advantage</li><li>No loss-chasing prompts, fake urgency, or autoplay by default</li></ul></article></section>
